^-|fp||ht|c|at|^B@2^Z@3^*BGame^*N: Is a contract whereby the declaring side commits to make at least 100 points. Because the value of each trick varies for suits and NT, therefore, partnership should make one of the following commitments.
^c@2In minors the commitment is 11 tricks. 6 (book) + 5 X 20 = 100. The first six tricks don't have any points.
In majors the commitment is 10 tricks. 6 (book) + 4 X 30 = 120. Each trick in majors is worth 30 points. That is 120 points which again is more than 100.
In NT the commitment is 9 tricks. 6 is free and the other three get 40 points for the first trick and 30 points for the other two. That is 100 points.

^b@2^*BPartscore^*N: When the pair commits to a contract which makes less than 100 it is called partscore. Contracts less than 5@C, 5@D, 4@H, 4@S, and 3N are partscores. The least commitment is 7 tricks in either suits or in NT.

^*BOvertrick(s)^*N and ^*BUndertricks^*N: The declaring side, on occasions, may make one or more tricks above the original commitment. The value of each additional trick is added to the final result. Conversely, the declaring side may fail to make the required number of tricks. The number of tricks by which they fail is the undertricks. For example, if they take 7 tricks in 3NT, the undertrick count is 2.

^*BVulnerability^*N: A key feature of duplicate bridge is the concept of vulnerability. Unlike rubber bridge, it is pre-determined depending only on the number of boards played. Vulnerability changes from board to board. One side will find its partnership vulnerable about 50 percent of the time. Sometimes neither partnership will be vulnerable; sometimes both will be vulnerable. This rotation is repeated every 4 boards. Vulnerability has significant impact on scoring and becomes an important factor in one's bidding and play strategies.

^*BGame or Bonus Points^*N: The declaring side in addition to the total points for the tricks they made, receive additional points according to the following chart: 
^C@2For a partscore ^g= 50 points
 ^cFor a game ^g= 300 points (non-vulnerable) / 500 points (vulnerable). If you bid and make game, you do not get the partscore bonus as well. 
 For small slam ^g= 500 points (non-vulnerable) / 750 (vulnerable) 
 For grand slam ^g= 1000 points (none-vulnerable) / 1500 (vulnerable).
