ht|b|fp|1|cs|6|at|^-{          MP/IMP Legends        }
^-|fp||ht|b|va|6|at|^B@2^Z@3In step (2) subtract each three opponents’ scores from the NS pair 1’s score as it was a team match:
A. NS pair 1 score vs NS pair 2 ---> 430 – 400 = 30
B. NS pair 1 score vs NS pair 3 ---> 430 – 150 =280
C. NS pair 1 score vs NS pair 4 ---> 430- (-50) = 480
                
In step (3) convert the subtractions in IMPs:
For A 30 we have 1 IMP
For B 280 we have 7 IMPs
For C 480 we have 10 IMPs

For step (4) sum the IMPs up and divide them by the number of opponents (3 here) and the result for the NS pair 1 is (1+7+10)/3 = 6 IMPs. The EW pair 1, who played this board on the same table with NS pair 1, will receive -6 IMPs accordingly.

Using the same steps the IMP scoring is done for all of the other pairs as shown below:

NS pair 2: ^eA. NS pair 2 score vs NS pair 1 ---> 400 - 430  = - 30 -1 IMPs
^eB. NS pair 2 score vs NS pair 3 ---> 400- 150   = 250   6 IMPs 
^eC. NS pair 2 score vs NS pair 4 ---> 400- (-50) = 450   10 IMPs
NS pair 2 receives (-1+ 6+ 10)/3 = 5  IMPs

NS pair 3:  ^eA. NS pair 3 score vs NS pair 1 ---> 150-430 = -280 -7 IMPs
^eB. NS pair 3 score vs NS pair 2 ---> 150-400 = -250 -6 IMPs
^eC. NS pair 3 score vs NS pair 4 ---> 150-(-50)= 200  5 IMPs
NS pair 3 receives [(-7-6)+5] = -8/3= -2.66 IMPs

NS pair 4: ^eA. NS pair 4 score vs NS pair 1 ---> -50 -430= -480 = -10 IMPs
^eB. NS pair 4 score vs NS pair 2 ---> -50 -400= -450 = -10 IMPs
^eC. NS pair 4 score vs NS pair 3 ---> -50 -150= -200 = -5 IMPs  
NS pair 4 receives (-10 -10-5)/3  = -8.33 IMPs
